issue.body:
During working on #12840 I discovered [autoload-dev](https://getcomposer.org/doc/04-schema.md#autoload-dev) section of Composer.

> `autoload-dev` (root-only)#
>
> This section allows to define autoload rules for development purposes.
>
> Classes needed to run the test suite should not be included in the main autoload rules to avoid polluting the autoloader in production and when other people use your package as a dependency.
>
> Therefore, it is a good idea to rely on a dedicated path for your unit tests and to add it within the `autoload-dev` section.
>
> Example:
>
> ```json
> {
>     "autoload": {
>         "psr-4": { "MyLibrary\\": "src/" }
>     },
>     "autoload-dev": {
>         "psr-4": { "MyLibrary\\Tests\\": "tests/" }
>     }
> }
> ```

We can add this to `composer.json`:

```json
"autoload-dev": {
    "psr-4": {
        "yiiunit\\": "tests/"
    }
},
```

and run `composer dump-autoload`.

Then this line in `tests/bootstrap.php` will become unnecessary:

```php
Yii::setAlias('@yiiunit', __DIR__);
```

Also want to ask about this block:

```php
// require composer autoloader if available
$composerAutoload = __DIR__ . '/../vendor/autoload.php';
if (is_file($composerAutoload)) {
    require_once($composerAutoload);
} else {
    require_once(__DIR__ . '/../../../autoload.php');
}
```

- Running `composer update` is a required condition in [Prepare testing environment](https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/master/docs/internals/git-workflow.md#3-prepare-the-testing-environment-) section of [Git workflow for Yii 2 contributors](https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/master/docs/internals/git-workflow.md).
- I think Composer is used in Travis too,

So is this check really needed?

Note that to ignore `autoload-dev` section on production, we need to use `--no-dev` flag (found it not in official docs, but in this [blog article](https://hannesvdvreken.com/2015/01/28/autoload-dev/)). We can cover this in docs.

For example in [Deployer](https://github.com/deployphp/deployer) deploy tool it's already considered in [common recipe](https://github.com/deployphp/deployer/blob/master/recipe/common.php):

```php
set('composer_options', '{{composer_action}} --verbose --prefer-dist --no-progress --no-interaction --no-dev --optimize-autoloader');
```

[Laravel](https://github.com/laravel/laravel/blob/master/composer.json) already uses it for tests.

So seems like this is a recommended way of handling autoloading in test environment in case of using Composer (and we use it for tests).

I can send a PR if you agree with this change.
